					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-102848#post-1382028</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-102848/forum-categories#post-1382028</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 26 Feb 2012 06:01:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Kimura Okagawa</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>398761</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It does, doesn't it?</p> <p>ahninjas: Here's my explanation on the &quot;anything is discussable&quot; phenomonon, copied from the Meta-Thread.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Officially,&nbsp;it&nbsp;should&nbsp;be&nbsp;pronounced&nbsp;'es-see-pee-ception',&nbsp;but&nbsp;'skipception'&nbsp;IS&nbsp;easier&nbsp;to&nbsp;say.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Wait,&nbsp;Class&nbsp;As&nbsp;are&nbsp;short-term&nbsp;memory,&nbsp;not&nbsp;Class&nbsp;B...</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>It's a glitch in the Wikidot Matrix. Every page on a wiki must have a discussion page. Even discussion pages. Hence the metathread: a discussion page for every discussion page and forum thread on the site, including itself. The graph of discussion pages has three levels and no loose nodes, with a single arrow pointing from a regular page to its discussion page, every discussion page and forum thread point to the metathread, and the metathread points to itself.</p> <p>Now go take a Class B before your brain implodes.</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
